{"id":"quant-ph/0509186","submitter":"Jonas S\\\"oderholm","authors":"Shigehiko Mori, Jonas Soderholm, Naoto Namekata, Shuichiro Inoue","title":"On the distribution of 1550-nm photon pairs efficiently generated using\n  a periodically poled lithium niobate waveguide","comments":"12 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":"Opt. Commun. 264 (2006) 156-162","doi":"10.1016/j.optcom.2006.02.010","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We report on the generation of photon pairs in the 1550-nm band suitable for\nlong-distance fiber-optic quantum key distribution. The photon pairs were\ngenerated in a periodically poled lithium niobate waveguide with a high\nconversion-efficiency. Using a pulsed semiconductor laser with a pulse rate of\n800 kHz and a maximum average pump power of 50 muW, we obtained a coincidence\nrate of 600 s^-1. Our measurements are in agreement with a Poissonian\nphoton-pair distribution, as is expected from a comparison of the coherence\ntime of the pump and of the detected photons. An average of 0.9 photon pairs\nper pulse was obtained.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Sep 2005 09:59:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
