{"id":"quant-ph/0509190","submitter":"Luis Moch\\'an","authors":"Ana M. Contreras-Reyes and W. Luis Moch\\'an","title":"Surface Screening in the Casimir Force","comments":"5 pages, 2 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A {\\bf 72}, 034102 (2005)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.72.034102","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We calculate the corrections to the Casimir force between two metals due to\nthe spatial dispersion of their response functions. We employ model-independent\nexpressions for the force in terms of the optical coefficients. We express the\nnon-local corrections to the Fresnel coefficients employing the surface\n$d_\\perp$ parameter, which accounts for the distribution of the surface\nscreening charge. Within a self-consistent jellium calculation, spatial\ndispersion increases the Casimir force significatively for small separations.\nThe nonlocal correction has the opposite sign than previously predicted\nemploying hydrodynamic models and assuming abruptly terminated surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Sep 2005 15:39:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
